reviews.text:
Terrible food. Terrible service. DO NOT EAT HERE. Go to the ground floor cafe/restaurant instead. 

If I could give 0 stars, I would. 

Sat at table 33, 3 persons. 

FOOD:
I ordered chicken cutlet Taiwanese rice. You would get better quality and better tasting food from KFC or McDonald's than here. 
I ordered it with the soup and Taiwan iced tea. The soup was ok but the drink was far too sweet and I even asked for less sweet when I ordered it. So they either didn't listen to my order or don't know how to make a drink to order. I also had a side of fried dumplings which tasted awful. I have no idea what they mixed with the meat but it was over bearing and I would also avoid this.

Wife ordered braised beef noodle soup with pig knuckle and shared some with our son. Nothing special about it, had better noodle soup in other restaurants. The beef however was more like the kind you make soup with than you serve to eat. Pig knuckle was flavourless and again had better elsewhere but would not recommend it either. 

Service:
There is no table service. Also our table wasn't even stable. It was wobbly. 
You are seated (or if it's quiet, you're welcome to find a seat) and told your table number for ordering. You go to the counter to order and pay. 

However, the manager asked us to move tables near the end of the meal so he could join 2 tables together for a group of 9 people. Really?! Your group of 9 is that more important? That is not customer service. If you waited 3 minutes, we would have left anyway.

Terrible food is everywhere but had he not done that, I'd not have written this review, or told the WhatsApp group for our building estate how terrible they were. I can only hope for them to quickly disappear and a better restaurant/cafe takes its place and serves the community because without community support, you won't survive.
What a shame..

滷蛋滷肉飯$42
港式泰國米配冇香味的滷肉和冇味的滷蛋
一點台式食物的感覺也沒有。
牛肉麵都ok！環境比想像中大和舒適！
食物不錯;地方寬敞

Nice mall, nice restaurant.  A bit packed with ground floor shopping stands.
Small plaza,  its clean and good for quiet dining
The Racing Hero for kids is just a joke. It is totally waste of time and money. The cars are mostly short of battery and the staff doesn’t care about the problem at all.

Glad this opened. It's so convenient. Would like some more variety in restaurants and some that are not so expensive. Great having a supermarket,  but the fruit and vegetable quality diminished quickly after opening.

reviews.text: 架構完整 清一色偏向食  欠觀光旅遊 可休養生息
食肆大部份都係質素麻麻，唔好有要求只求飽肚都可接受既。提供穿梭巴士方法小家子，一張單不論幾錢都只能換一張飛。彈床玩樂海鮮價，明明4日都做全日任玩，無端白事第二日換一個場景後加$20，扮晒復活節特別活動咁。

第一次經過此商場
有好多兒童遊樂場設施
但沒想到商場 9點差不多所有店鋪已關門，好冷清
